    <item>
      <title>Election 2016: AMA concedes restoring $57 billion to hospitals 'difficult'</title>
      <link>http://www.smh.com.au/federal-politics/federal-election-2016/election-2016-ama-concedes-restoring-57-billion-to-hospitals-difficult-20160512-gotc6e.html</link>

      <title>Slow ambulances and injury-prone paramedics in NSW</title>
      <link>http://www.smh.com.au/nsw/slow-ambulances-and-injuryprone-paramedics-in-nsw-20160507-gooazr.html</link>
      <description><p><img src="http://images.smh.com.au/2016/05/07/7402087/Thumbnail100890359111v23himage.related.thumbnail.320x214.gooazr.png1462645850831.jpg-90x60.jpg" width="90" height="60" style="float:left;margin:4px;border:0px"/></p>Ambulances are slower to respond to life threatening situations in NSW than any other jurisdiction bar Tasmania, with the most under-staffed service on the eastern seaboard.</description>

    <item>
      <title>Information overload poses health risks during pregnancy</title>
      <link>http://www.smh.com.au/national/health/information-overload-poses-health-risks-during-pregnancy-20160507-gonz9c.html</link>
      <description><p><img src="http://images.smh.com.au/2016/05/07/7401839/Thumbnail1008888384goorhyimage.related.thumbnail.320x214.gonz9c.png1462618825060.jpg-90x60.jpg" width="90" height="60" style="float:left;margin:4px;border:0px"/></p>Avoid soft cheese. Avoid deli meats. No pate, no bean sprouts. Eat well-cooked meat but not burnt. Don't eat stuffing. These are just a few of the dozens of recommendations in brochures and booklets routinely given to pregnant women.</description>
